003cp\u003eIn 1439, a goldsmith named Johannes Gutenberg was working on an ill-begotten project to create polished metal mirrors designed to capture the holy light from religious relics, to be sold to pilgrims visiting an exhibition in Aachen, Germany. However, after flooding led to the event being delayed by a year, Gutenberg found himself out of money, and instead turned to his other project, a press that would use movable type to mechanize the process of printing books. - John Walker \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/daemonologie-indie-pc-steam-horror-witchfinder-1851667495\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/daemonologie-indie-pc-steam-horror-witchfinder-1851667495\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"87a65e9d7c54ff9e10082d25e99f4ef5\" data-recommend-id=\"image://87a65e9d7c54ff9e10082d25e99f4ef5\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1279\" data-height=\"720\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A group of nuns with halos laugh at a halo-less nun\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"A group of nuns with halos laugh at a halo-less nun\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/87a65e9d7c54ff9e10082d25e99f4ef5.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/87a65e9d7c54ff9e10082d25e99f4ef5.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/87a65e9d7c54ff9e10082d25e99f4ef5.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A group of nuns with halos laugh at a halo-less nun\" data-chomp-id=\"87a65e9d7c54ff9e10082d25e99f4ef5\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"720\" data-alt=\"A group of nuns with halos laugh at a halo-less nun\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/87a65e9d7c54ff9e10082d25e99f4ef5.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: 11 bit studios\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"87a65e9d7c54ff9e10082d25e99f4ef5\" data-recommend-id=\"image://87a65e9d7c54ff9e10082d25e99f4ef5\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1279\" data-height=\"720\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A group of nuns with halos laugh at a halo-less nun\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e2024 has been a year of many \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/best-video-games-2024-pc-ps5-xbox-switch-1851291118\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/best-video-games-2024-pc-ps5-xbox-switch-1851291118\"\u003ebig releases\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, and I’ve played quite a lot of them, which means plenty more games inevitably fall through the cracks. It’s rare that, during a busy release year, I get a chance to check out a game months after it came out, and it’s even more rare that I fall in love with it. But that’s exactly what happened when I got around to playing \u003cem\u003eIndika\u003c/em\u003e, a third-person adventure game that was released back in May. Now, I can’t believe I waited so long to experience it. \u003cem\u003eIndika \u003c/em\u003eis one of the most fascinating releases of the year, blending friction-filled gameplay with a narrative that dissects religious trauma. - Willa Rowe \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/indika-steam-pc-nun-narrative-adventure-1851669861\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/indika-steam-pc-nun-narrative-adventure-1851669861\" data-vtas-click=\"self:InlineUrl:inline-url-postbody\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"71576a57df8f540d832142f4736baec3\" data-recommend-id=\"image://71576a57df8f540d832142f4736baec3\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1139\" data-height=\"641\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A man wearing glasses and a red button up stands in front of a red background\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"A man wearing glasses and a red button up stands in front of a red background\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/71576a57df8f540d832142f4736baec3.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/71576a57df8f540d832142f4736baec3.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/71576a57df8f540d832142f4736baec3.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A man wearing glasses and a red button up stands in front of a red background\" data-chomp-id=\"71576a57df8f540d832142f4736baec3\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"641\" data-alt=\"A man wearing glasses and a red button up stands in front of a red background\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/71576a57df8f540d832142f4736baec3.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: Blue Rider Interactive\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"71576a57df8f540d832142f4736baec3\" data-recommend-id=\"image://71576a57df8f540d832142f4736baec3\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1139\" data-height=\"641\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A man wearing glasses and a red button up stands in front of a red background\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eOne of the most well-known principles of theatrical storytelling is widely referred to as “Chekhov’s gun.” The principle suggests that if some element is introduced to a story, even in a casual, offhand way, by the end, it had better prove significant. Or, as it’s often summed up, if a gun shows up at some point in your story, by the end, it had better go off. So, when a gun shows up early in my playthrough of narrative game \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/games/apartment-story\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/games/apartment-story\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eApartment Story\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003e,\u003c/em\u003e you can imagine where my mind immediately went. - Willa Rowe \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/apartment-story-pc-sims-suspense-chekhov-godot-1851667761\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/apartment-story-pc-sims-suspense-chekhov-godot-1851667761\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
